caption.body: Pan Am Express was a subsidiary of Pan American World Airways primarily focused on connecting passengers to Pan Am's hub at John F. Kennedy International Airport (JFK) for Latin American and trans-Atlantic routes, but also provided regional services in many other areas of the U.S., as well as the Bahamas and Europe.  Did you ever fly on Pan Am Express?  Image: Pan American World Airways postcard, Aérospatiale ATR-42, 1987. Gift of the Captain John B. Russell Family. 2012.149.0442
